Reasoning: The problem of computing isomorphisms and embeddings of finite fields is a central problem in computer algebra and has applications in coding theory, cryptography, and computational geometry. Therefore, it could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.SC (Symbolic Computation), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
